node.text: "But if we learned anything from sports, is that no matter how far down we may be, we are never too far down to come back."
The Houston-based rapper brings his workwear touch to Nike SB, adding bandana patterns, rope-style fat laces, and more to the fat-tongued gem.

node.title: Unboxing Travis Scott's Nike SB Dunk collaboration

node.text: @kyrieirving calls his upcoming Nike Kyrie 8 shoes "trash". Upon seeing leaked images on @k11kicks, Kyrie Irving pans the shoe, claims to have no involvement in design/marketing, and apologizes to his fans. While athletes not liking their shoes is nothing new (MJ, LeBron, Wade, etc. have all been critical), this typically occurs behind closed doors. Hit the link in our bio for more details on this eye-opening development.

node.text: Lauded for its innovation, yet derided for its lack of accessibility to those truly in need, the Nike Go FlyEase is set to return to retail in a new red/black colorway. No word on how Nike will handle the release, although all eyes will be on how brand tackles the issue. Hit the link in our bio to see a closer look.
